value.0: Her ever watchful eyes keep a close mark on all the Shadowflame house treasures. Careful to never lose track of the families most precious jewels.

Value.value: Hello, I'm Cloe Shadowflame. I store the Shadowflames most valued assets. Do you have an item or two you would like to deposit into our treasury?

value.0: The man that stands before you appears to have years of experience in battle. He stands strong and true as a Shadowflame trainer for all sorts of weapon mastery styles. Though the glisten of his eyes and set expression lets those that approach for his aid know, he will not go easy and will push each Shadowflame to be their best.

Value.value: Give it all you've got!
You've got to push yourself if you want to survive in battle.
Show me what you can do.
When you're ready, you'll take on Shale.
Your weapon is only an instrument you play.
Control it! Don't let it control you.
Need a shoulder to lean on or a sympathetic ear? I have a pair of each!
Dark, creamy, light, and bubbly. You name it, I serve it.

There I was... looking straight into the belly of this beast with one grumbling stomach when I saw it... something in that bowl swiveled, and I swear I saw an eye roll back in the soup! Haven't touched Ruddy's soups since...
No ale in the world can get the taste of Ruddy's cookin' outta my mouth.
Pull up a stool and tell me what ales ya.

value.0: The gnome before you holds a curious and welcoming grin unlike any other you've seen before. While the wings are a dead give away that this isn't your standard run of the mill gnome, the endless banter and curious combination of scents and supplies about the kitchen just strengthens your first instinct that he isn't normal. As social as can be, Ruddy is as excited as can be when one enters the kitchen or dining hall.

Value.value: Fish egg soup! It's perfect... it will be the next finest delicacy known to mankind and it started right here!

A little butter, some seasonings, fry until it just begins to turn tough and wa-la! Toss the tongue between two pieces of bread and slap on some cheese and you have a mouth watering treat. You want to try some, no?
I'll cook you up whatever you desire! Just don't tell Rose... she gets real sensitive when people like my food over hers.

value.0: A slightly round and overly excited young gnome smiles eagerly up at you. Her skin appears to have a very slight copper tint to it and her eyes are lit up with absolute joy while in the kitchen. The very scent of her cooking is enough to make a full mans stomach grumble for more.

Value.value: Good thing I didn't marry him for his cooking skills...
Lizards tongues... *grumbles* who in their right mind makes a sandwich out of lizard tongues?!
Care for some fresh cookies dear? I promise those are raisins and not.. well... they're raisins.
What can I get for you dear? Perhaps some of the fresh slow cooked pot roast with savory herbs I have here?
It blinked! I looked at his soup and something in it blinked at me!

value.0:
The back of this helm is marked with the Shadowflame Insignia. The helm lets Shadowflame history show in it's ability to see through darkness and cast it as well.

With a command word, the wearer can bring forth a darkness effect.  The power issues from the various treasured gems kept within the family.
This ordinary-looking helmet appears slightly worn and battered.
Forged with the Shadowflame House insignia imprinted upon it. This flaming sword strikes against foes with what the house is known for; strength, honor, and unity.
From the forge of Shadowflame Manor, this fire resistant shield can be seen upon all Royal Guards. Enchanted by sorcerers to protect from spells as the holder faces various opponents.

Value.value: Move on, move on! I haven't got all day.

value.0: The Shadowflame has a special division within their home known as the Royal Guards, which consists of fighters, archers, shadow dancers, and mages. These robes are designed for the mages, to protect them from fire as well as other spells.

Value.value: Sally truly is gifted... I just hope she doesn't light the next house cat on fire.. poor fluffy, never seen a flaming furr ball before. Oh! It lived, it'll be okay... just bald.
It truly is a blessing when another can grow from my words.
To know ones history is to know what to expect in the future.
